y accessing a missing key returns None or a default value.\"\n\nThis is testable:\n```python\ndef test_missing_key_returns_none():\n    config_yaml = \"key1: value1\"\n    with patch('builtins.open', mock_open(read_data=config_yaml)):\n        config = loader.load_config()\n        assert config.get('missing_key') is None\n```\n\nGood. This assumes the loader returns a dict-like object that supports .get(). If it's a custom class, the test might need adjustment.\n\nI think I have a solid set of test cases now. Let me finalize the test file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13298,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13298},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bfd9091-9e57-409c-8955-d6e89a7f6aee","uuid":"b072153f-29b5-4f3b-98a2-8083458e603e"}
